FBIS3-15906 "drsov048_b_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-048 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues TV Reports Kremlin Meeting LD1003185294 Moscow Nezavisimoye Televideniye Television in Russian 1600 GMT 10 Mar 94 LD1003185294 Moscow Nezavisimoye Televideniye Television Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Yeltsin is concerned at the absence of civic concord in the country. This was the theme of talks held today in the Kremlin. [Correspondent Mitkeviecus] Today, the president gathered together in the Kremlin representatives of public political movements, parties, Duma factions, the church, Federation Council, and government in order to develop an agreement on civic peace. [Begin Yeltsin recording] [Words indistinct] some kind of single opinion, or several common positions that will unite us in society -- namely, civic peace and concord, civic positions in society -- so people understand us, that we are not working against Russia, we are not working against Russians, but are in favor of this concord, that the time for confrontation has passed. [end recording] [passage omitted]
